nTokenRedeem(address,uint16,uint96,bool).notice: Allows accounts to redeem nTokens into constituent assets and then absorb the assets into their portfolio. Due to the complexity here, it is not allowed to be called during a batch trading operation and must be done separately.

params.redeemer: the address that holds the nTokens to redeem
params.sellTokenAssets: attempt to sell residual fCash and convert to cash, if unsuccessful then residual fCash assets will be placed into the portfolio
params.tokensToRedeem_: the amount of nTokens to convert to cash

returns._0: total amount of asset cash redeemed

nTokenRedeemViaBatch(uint16,int256).notice: When redeeming nTokens via the batch they must all be sold to cash and this method will return the amount of asset cash sold. This method can only be invoked via delegatecall.

params.tokensToRedeem: the amount of nTokens to convert to cash

returns._0: amount of asset cash to return to the account, denominated in internal token decimals
